1
00:00:13,060 --> 00:00:13,890
Come in.

2
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:17,500
All the loose ends have been tied up.

3
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:19,180
The driver has been
sent out of the capital.

4
00:00:26,410 --> 00:00:28,930
What do you think of today's show?

5
00:00:29,220 --> 00:00:30,969
Yuan Hong took the drink can in
for testing.

6
00:00:30,970 --> 00:00:32,470
He's already suspicious.

7
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:33,790
The Marshal's shipment with the Japanese

8
00:00:33,790 --> 00:00:35,500
=Cases Between Us=
has also arrived at Tianjin Port.

9
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:37,369
=Episode 28=

10
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,609
Since they love digging,

11
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:40,540
let them dig as much as they like.

12
00:00:43,690 --> 00:00:45,610
Do you know what makes the best show?

13
00:00:47,330 --> 00:00:49,330
It's not about star-crossed lovers.

14
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:52,539
A father and son
turning against each other.

15
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:54,500
Brothers becoming enemies.

16
00:00:54,610 --> 00:00:57,139
Once Yuan Hong traces it back
to the Japanese,

17
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,499
he'll discover

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,819
that his own father

19
00:00:59,820 --> 00:01:01,820
is the biggest link in the chain.

20
00:01:07,490 --> 00:01:08,899
What's that old fox Zhao Chengru

21
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:10,370
been up to lately?

22
00:01:11,460 --> 00:01:13,129
He's been swamped dealing with

23
00:01:13,130 --> 00:01:14,900
the Ministry of Education's funding.

24
00:01:17,610 --> 00:01:20,129
See? You don't even have
to do anything yourself.

25
00:01:20,130 --> 00:01:22,609
Just poke a tiny hole
in the paper window,

26
00:01:22,610 --> 00:01:25,500
and the north wind
will tear it wide open.

27
00:01:34,050 --> 00:01:37,500
This is a blood jade thumb ring
from the Qianlong era.

28
00:01:37,690 --> 00:01:39,500
Watch closely.

29
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:42,760
Mr. Zhang,

30
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:45,379
(Zhang Baochen, owner of Canglong House)
that jade pendant from the Ma's Jade Shop

31
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:46,489
has an offer

32
00:01:46,490 --> 00:01:48,290
of 20,000 silver coins.

33
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:50,370
That jade pendant?

34
00:01:51,610 --> 00:01:52,900
Someone's actually buying it?

35
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:55,140
Why not?

36
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:57,170
Come on.

37
00:01:58,020 --> 00:02:01,170
Haven't you heard
about the Ma family's curse?

38
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:03,220
What happened?

39
00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:07,739
Forget it.

40
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:08,769
Forget it.

41
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:10,179
It's late now.

42
00:02:10,180 --> 00:02:10,979
Let's talk about

43
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:11,769
something else.

44
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:12,899
Come on.

45
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,300
Tell me.

46
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:15,970
Shall I?

47
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:17,340
Let's hear it.

48
00:02:18,770 --> 00:02:19,899
Back in the Year of Gengzi,

49
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,810
when the Westerner troops
entered Beijing,

50
00:02:22,210 --> 00:02:24,209
Master Ma Xiangde

51
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:26,329
was a Bannerman.

52
00:02:26,330 --> 00:02:27,699
He fled west with his family,

53
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:30,650
escorting the Empress Dowager to safety.

54
00:02:31,210 --> 00:02:34,020
His father was still alive

55
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:36,259
but too ill

56
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:37,500
to leave.

57
00:02:37,610 --> 00:02:39,329
Before they departed,

58
00:02:39,330 --> 00:02:41,609
he gave Master Ma

59
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:45,300
a blood jade pendant
bestowed by the Qianlong Emperor.

60
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:46,739
The jade

61
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:49,019
had been unearthed from a Han tomb.

62
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:52,460
It belonged to Liu Bang,
Emperor Gaozu of Han.

63
00:02:58,330 --> 00:02:59,419
What's so funny?

64
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:01,049
The Emperor robbed tombs too?

65
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:02,899
Is that really true?

66
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:03,970
Alright.

67
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,019
Forget I said anything.

68
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:05,649
Forget it.

69
00:03:05,650 --> 00:03:06,739
No.

70
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:07,899
Go on.

71
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:10,580
I'll just treat it as a story.

72
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:15,979
Master Ma

73
00:03:15,980 --> 00:03:18,300
traveled west with his whole family.

74
00:03:18,530 --> 00:03:20,809
Along the way, they faced famine

75
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:22,500
and bandits.

76
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:33,650
By the time they reached Shaanxi,

77
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,459
Master Ma was out of food.

78
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:36,810
He was at the end of his rope.

79
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:38,489
He was just about to take his own life.

80
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:39,649
Guess what happened?

81
00:03:39,650 --> 00:03:41,459
He suddenly felt

82
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:43,580
a burning sensation in his chest.

83
00:03:43,650 --> 00:03:45,020
He took off the pendant

84
00:03:46,490 --> 00:03:48,370
and saw it glowing red

85
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:51,049
in the dark.

86
00:03:51,050 --> 00:03:52,859
Whether it's true or not
is anyone's guess.

87
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:54,500
But Master Ma claimed

88
00:03:54,580 --> 00:03:58,530
the spirit inside the jade spoke to him.

89
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:00,900
It told him to hang on a little longer,

90
00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:04,489
and the ordeal would soon pass.

91
00:04:04,490 --> 00:04:05,810
A jade spirit?

92
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:08,340
Ancient jade is said to have a spirit.

93
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:10,489
If it's properly cared for,
it'll protect its owner

94
00:04:10,490 --> 00:04:11,859
and ward off misfortune.

95
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,410
Not long after that,

96
00:04:13,650 --> 00:04:14,609
Master Ma

97
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:16,290
came into a fortune.

98
00:04:16,330 --> 00:04:18,849
He returned to Beijing
and opened a jade shop.

99
00:04:18,850 --> 00:04:20,819
From then on, he prospered.

100
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,460
It's a good omen.

101
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,579
Well,

102
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:27,380
it depends on how you look at it.

103
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:29,900
The Ma family got rich,

104
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:31,139
but it came

105
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:33,820
at Master Ma's expense.

106
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:37,139
At the height of his success,

107
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:39,410
he was struck by a strange illness.

108
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:41,059
He lost his mind

109
00:04:41,060 --> 00:04:42,169
and didn't live

110
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:43,499
much longer.

111
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,899
And that wasn't the end of it.

112
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:47,059
His descendants suffered too.

113
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:48,259
His daughter

114
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:50,089
was childless for years

115
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,379
and was eventually divorced.

116
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:54,379
His son became a gambler

117
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:56,619
and lost the family fortune.

118
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:58,209
The jade shop was all they had left.

119
00:04:58,210 --> 00:04:59,729
If things weren't that bad,

120
00:04:59,730 --> 00:05:01,940
why would they sell the pendant?

121
00:05:06,020 --> 00:05:07,290
What a tragedy.

122
00:05:08,530 --> 00:05:10,729
Don't scare me.

123
00:05:10,730 --> 00:05:12,939
You made all that up, didn't you?

124
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:15,260
Have I ever joked
about something like this?

125
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:18,530
Do you know how blood jade is made?

126
00:05:19,770 --> 00:05:23,220
It's nourished
with the blood of the dead.

127
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:26,940
To put it nicely,

128
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:28,650
they call it a jade spirit.

129
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:30,380
But in reality,

130
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:33,819
it could be some evil spirits

131
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,290
from who knows what dynasty.

132
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:40,020
Once it latches onto you,

133
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:44,259
you'll drain your blood and your luck

134
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:46,410
to repay its debts.

135
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:51,579
Enough talk.

136
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:52,259
Mr. Zhang,

137
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:53,379
name your price.

138
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:54,850
I'll take the money and leave.

139
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:00,380
Alright.

140
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:01,940
I will give you

141
00:06:02,730 --> 00:06:04,020
this much.

142
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:07,700
Three thousand is too low.

143
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,650
Hundred.

144
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:12,170
How much?

145
00:06:12,290 --> 00:06:14,529
You're louder than the thunder.

146
00:06:14,530 --> 00:06:16,020
Three hundred.

147
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,819
You're just trying to rip me off.

148
00:06:18,820 --> 00:06:20,769
Oh, I'm trying to save you.

149
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:22,169
How's that ripping you off?

150
00:06:22,170 --> 00:06:24,289
Think about it.
Who used to wear thumb rings like this?

151
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:25,289
Warriors.

152
00:06:25,290 --> 00:06:26,849
They wore them when drawing a bow.

153
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:29,259
How many souls died to those arrows?

154
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:30,769
How much kamic debt do they carry?

155
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:33,730
Aren't you afraid
those spirits might possess you?

156
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:04,170
Who's there?

157
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,459
Over here.

158
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:21,920
(Ma's Jade Shop)

159
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:23,850
Yuzhen.

160
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:26,290
Yuzhen, open up.

161
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:28,379
Yuzhen, why did you lock the door?

162
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,139
It's me.

163
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:29,819
Yuzhen.

164
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:31,379
(Ma's Jade Shop)
Open up, Yuzhen. It's me.

165
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,289
Move.

166
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:33,290
I'll handle this.

167
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:44,050
Yuzhen.

168
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:45,290
Yuzhen.

169
00:07:45,410 --> 00:07:46,610
Yuzhen!

170
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:48,329
What's wrong, Yuzhen?

171
00:07:48,330 --> 00:07:49,059
Yuzhen!

172
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:50,610
Don't scare me.

173
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:53,820
Yuzhen...

174
00:08:17,460 --> 00:08:18,619
Since we got married,

175
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:22,490
I would pick Yuzhen up from the shop
every night at eight.

176
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,000
Yesterday was no different.

177
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,169
(Chang Fei)

178
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:27,460
But when I got back...

179
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:33,420
Yuzhen.

180
00:08:41,570 --> 00:08:42,339
Uh.

181
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:43,420
Yuzhen.

182
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:44,970
Yuzhen.

183
00:08:45,690 --> 00:08:46,730
Yuzhen.

184
00:08:47,740 --> 00:08:49,300
What's wrong, Yuzhen?

185
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:50,409
Are you alright?

186
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:52,619
(Ma Yuzhen, owner of Ma's Jade Shop)
I'm fine. You...

187
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:54,060
Call the police.

188
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:56,420
Who's there?

189
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:02,970
Who?

190
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:09,769
That person ran too fast.

191
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:11,060
I couldn't catch him.

192
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,619
Then I did what Yuzhen told me to

193
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:14,490
and came straight to the station.

194
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:16,700
This officer took the report.

195
00:09:17,450 --> 00:09:19,769
The report was filed at 8:10 PM.

196
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:21,099
I got to the jade shop

197
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,490
at 8:20 PM.

198
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:26,490
What was stolen?

199
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,379
This is our inventory catalog.

200
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:33,730
I've checked it.

201
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:36,739
Five ancient jades and our heirloom,
the blood jade pendant,

202
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:38,219
are gone.

203
00:09:38,220 --> 00:09:40,409
33 of the 107 jade carvings

204
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:41,859
are missing,

205
00:09:41,860 --> 00:09:43,569
not counting the ones that were smashed.

206
00:09:43,570 --> 00:09:44,409
(Blood Jade Pendant,
Green Jade Landscape Inkstone)

207
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:45,409
The Ma family

208
00:09:45,410 --> 00:09:47,379
has quite a collection.

209
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:48,169
Look.

210
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:50,610
The landscape jade inkstone
is practically a national inkstone.

211
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,649
Practically?

212
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:53,610
Yeah.

213
00:09:53,650 --> 00:09:54,499
Lu Zigang,

214
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,970
the famed Ming dynasty jade carver.

215
00:09:56,140 --> 00:09:57,899
No one could match his craftsmanship.

216
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:58,899
This inkstone

217
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,380
once belonged to Zhang Juzheng.

218
00:10:00,380 --> 00:10:02,689
One corner was chipped when his estate
was confiscated, then restored later.

219
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:04,060
Otherwise, I'd have bought it.

220
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:12,680
(Hongfeng Insurance Company)

221
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:14,340
Hongfeng Insurance?

222
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:18,019
Those photos were taken
when we insured the collection.

223
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:20,099
The appraiser

224
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:21,820
made an extra set for us.

225
00:10:23,810 --> 00:10:26,139
Is everything in your shop insured?

226
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:27,259
At the beginning of the year,

227
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,890
that clothing store
on Wangfu Street caught fire.

228
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,809
Thanks to Hongfeng Insurance,

229
00:10:31,810 --> 00:10:33,379
they were fully compensated.

230
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,019
After that,

231
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:35,619
Yuzhen insured the shop.

232
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:37,730
It gave us some peace of mind.

233
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:40,460
Have we established
Ma Yuzhen's time of death?

234
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:42,809
Based on the autopsy
and witness statements,

235
00:10:42,810 --> 00:10:43,739
she died between 8 PM

236
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:45,340
and 8:15 PM.

237
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:48,770
Let's check out the shop.

238
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:08,569
This thief knew what he was doing.

239
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,460
He only took the valuable pieces.

240
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:13,220
Look.

241
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:15,370
The cracked pieces were left behind.

242
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,580
Looks like the thief knows jade trade.

243
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:26,250
Not just jade,

244
00:11:27,170 --> 00:11:28,940
he knows this shop

245
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,250
inside out.

246
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,379
He even knew

247
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:36,049
he could end up taking nothing,

248
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:37,970
even though he could pry open the lock.

249
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,420
An inside job?

250
00:11:46,530 --> 00:11:49,169
Could it be that Chang Fei
staged the whole thing

251
00:11:49,170 --> 00:11:50,730
and killed his wife for the insurance?

252
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:53,289
The policy isn't under Ma Yuzhen's name.

253
00:11:53,290 --> 00:11:54,569
If he were after money,

254
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:56,160
wouldn't it make more sense

255
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,920
to buy personal accident insurance
for himself?

256
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:59,010
Mr. Chang.

257
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:03,610
Where did you see the thief?

258
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,619
I heard a noise first.

259
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:06,859
I was inside a room.

260
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:09,300
As soon as I heard it, I rushed out.

261
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:10,219
The moment he saw me,

262
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,219
he bolted

263
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:13,060
and ran straight upstairs.

264
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,019
I panicked

265
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:17,289
and hesitated for a second.

266
00:12:17,290 --> 00:12:19,569
By the time I came to my senses
and chased after him,

267
00:12:19,570 --> 00:12:20,499
all I saw

268
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:23,220
was his back
as he disappeared into the alley.

269
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:24,970
Probably one of the shop assistants.

270
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:26,820
How do you know?

271
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:30,019
If it were an outsider, the quickest way out
would've been through the window.

272
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,800
But there's no sign
anyone climbed through it.

273
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,920
Also, going out the front door
would've been way too conspicuous.

274
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:36,099
He knew he just had to run upstairs,
cross the terrace,

275
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:38,049
and he'd be in Zanhua Alley
in just a few steps.

276
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:38,859
Have you

277
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,409
been to our shop before?

278
00:12:40,410 --> 00:12:41,049
No.

279
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:42,899
I visit Canglong House all the time.

280
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,580
I've seen your staff at work.

281
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,610
Right.

282
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:49,300
Now that you mention it,

283
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:51,529
that figure did look familiar.

284
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:53,649
We've got an assistant named Shunzi.

285
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:55,649
That build, the haircut,

286
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:57,010
and the way he moved

287
00:12:57,450 --> 00:12:58,970
all looked like him.

288
00:13:00,650 --> 00:13:01,339
Yang Dezhi.

289
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:02,169
Yes, sir.

290
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:03,420
Bring Shunzi in.

291
00:13:06,237 --> 00:13:09,797
(Jingshi Police Department)

292
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,440
(Shunzi, shop assistant at Ma's Jade Shop)
I was wrong, officers.

293
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,769
I stole the jade inkstone.

294
00:13:18,770 --> 00:13:20,370
I won't do it again.

295
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:21,809
Get up.

296
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:23,219
A man

297
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,169
doesn't kneel so easily.

298
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:25,289
You're not a servant.

299
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,370
Sit.

300
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:32,970
Where's the stolen item?

301
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:34,300
At my house.

302
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:37,890
My mother is gravely ill.

303
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,580
The physician said

304
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:42,130
she has only a couple of months left.

305
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:43,569
I didn't have enough money.

306
00:13:43,569 --> 00:13:45,760
I couldn't scrape together the money
for the medical bills.

307
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,970
Last night,

308
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:48,619
I lost my head.

309
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:49,929
You only stole this one?

310
00:13:49,930 --> 00:13:51,130
Just this one.

311
00:14:15,810 --> 00:14:17,449
All the antique jades

312
00:14:17,450 --> 00:14:19,099
were kept in a German-made

313
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:20,730
iron safe.

314
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,580
How did you open the combination lock?

315
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:26,730
I didn't.

316
00:14:26,783 --> 00:14:27,812
Who did?

317
00:14:27,813 --> 00:14:28,942
It really wasn't me.

318
00:14:28,943 --> 00:14:30,492
There weren't many customers last night.

319
00:14:30,493 --> 00:14:31,812
Since I live nearby,

320
00:14:31,813 --> 00:14:32,732
Ms. Ma

321
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,302
let me go home for dinner

322
00:14:34,303 --> 00:14:36,863
and come back later to lock up.

323
00:14:41,853 --> 00:14:42,813
Ms. Ma.

324
00:14:46,213 --> 00:14:47,263
Ms. Ma.

325
00:15:08,813 --> 00:15:10,623
I wanted to sell it for cash,

326
00:15:10,693 --> 00:15:13,262
so I took it to Mr. Zhang
at Canglong House.

327
00:15:13,263 --> 00:15:14,182
What time was that?

328
00:15:14,183 --> 00:15:15,343
7:30 PM.

329
00:15:15,783 --> 00:15:16,612
The moment

330
00:15:16,613 --> 00:15:18,053
he questioned me,

331
00:15:18,093 --> 00:15:19,262
I panicked.

332
00:15:19,263 --> 00:15:21,212
I grabbed the jade inkstone and ran home.

333
00:15:21,213 --> 00:15:23,343
I never left the house after that.

334
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:24,933
Can anyone prove that?

335
00:15:25,853 --> 00:15:26,662
Yes.

336
00:15:26,663 --> 00:15:27,972
I ran into Mrs. Qi

337
00:15:27,973 --> 00:15:29,142
in the alley.

338
00:15:29,143 --> 00:15:30,583
You can ask her.

339
00:15:30,973 --> 00:15:31,902
That's right.

340
00:15:31,903 --> 00:15:34,182
I saw Shunzi last night.

341
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:34,942
It was

342
00:15:34,943 --> 00:15:36,612
just after 7:30 PM.

343
00:15:36,613 --> 00:15:39,053
He was panicked

344
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:40,983
when he came rushing
out of Mao'er Alley.

345
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:42,422
Are you sure it was 7:30 PM?

346
00:15:42,423 --> 00:15:43,533
I am.

347
00:15:45,093 --> 00:15:46,103
Watch closely.

348
00:15:46,843 --> 00:15:47,662
What do you even know?

349
00:15:47,663 --> 00:15:49,103
What?

350
00:15:49,213 --> 00:15:49,812
Got it?

351
00:15:49,813 --> 00:15:51,092
Blood jade.

352
00:15:51,093 --> 00:15:52,463
Mr. Zhang.

353
00:15:54,973 --> 00:15:56,133
Young Master Zhao.

354
00:15:56,943 --> 00:15:57,983
You!

355
00:15:58,213 --> 00:15:59,263
Who did this?

356
00:15:59,613 --> 00:16:01,533
Who did this to you?

357
00:16:01,613 --> 00:16:02,893
Tell me who did this.

358
00:16:03,183 --> 00:16:04,413
I'll kill him.

359
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:05,692
Tell me now,

360
00:16:05,693 --> 00:16:08,212
and he won't live to see tomorrow.

361
00:16:08,213 --> 00:16:10,583
How dare he do this
to Young Master Zhao?

362
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:11,382
Enough.

363
00:16:11,383 --> 00:16:12,813
Cut that out.

364
00:16:13,573 --> 00:16:15,332
Save the crocodile tears.

365
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,463
No.

366
00:16:16,613 --> 00:16:18,452
- I mean it.
- If I were hurt,

367
00:16:18,453 --> 00:16:19,262
you'd be laughing

368
00:16:19,263 --> 00:16:20,703
from five li away.

369
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:22,653
You're actually laughing?

370
00:16:23,213 --> 00:16:23,422
No.

371
00:16:23,423 --> 00:16:24,572
I just thought of

372
00:16:24,573 --> 00:16:25,863
something funny.

373
00:16:28,783 --> 00:16:29,933
Mr. Zhang,

374
00:16:30,143 --> 00:16:31,202
you've struck gold again?

375
00:16:31,202 --> 00:16:33,092
Snag another bargain?
Come on. Let me take a look.

376
00:16:33,093 --> 00:16:33,612
No.

377
00:16:33,613 --> 00:16:34,852
That little thing

378
00:16:34,853 --> 00:16:36,133
is rough.

379
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:37,533
Take it out.

380
00:16:38,383 --> 00:16:39,503
Mr. Zhao,

381
00:16:39,613 --> 00:16:42,662
I never do business with Westerners.

382
00:16:42,663 --> 00:16:44,813
I'd appreciate it
if you'd stop bothering me.

383
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,400
Putting taro juice
on the jade thumb ring again?

384
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,242
As soon as they start itching, you tell them
it's haunted, then buy it for a song.

385
00:16:52,242 --> 00:16:53,640
Can't you come up with a new trick?

386
00:16:53,693 --> 00:16:55,542
Shut it. That's a vicious accusation.

387
00:16:55,543 --> 00:16:56,413
Dazhuang.

388
00:16:58,613 --> 00:16:59,583
It's okay.

389
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,852
I don't deal with contemporary pieces.

390
00:17:01,853 --> 00:17:02,612
Take it away.

391
00:17:02,613 --> 00:17:03,542
Take it away.

392
00:17:03,543 --> 00:17:04,703
Zhang Baochen,

393
00:17:05,863 --> 00:17:06,960
you're suspected of murder.

394
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,800
Come with me to the police station
and cooperate with the investigation.

395
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:09,942
Who? Me?

396
00:17:09,943 --> 00:17:10,492
You.

397
00:17:10,493 --> 00:17:10,862
Me?

398
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:12,240
Who did I kill?

399
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,622
Young Master Zhao, you can't use
your authority to settle a personal grudge.

400
00:17:14,623 --> 00:17:16,292
Fine, I admit it.
I talked behind your back.

401
00:17:16,293 --> 00:17:17,663
You talked behind my back?

402
00:17:19,213 --> 00:17:20,102
You did?

403
00:17:20,103 --> 00:17:20,862
Did I?

404
00:17:20,863 --> 00:17:21,822
You did.

405
00:17:21,823 --> 00:17:22,422
I didn't.

406
00:17:22,423 --> 00:17:22,862
You did.

407
00:17:22,863 --> 00:17:23,292
I didn't.

408
00:17:23,293 --> 00:17:23,862
Fine.

409
00:17:23,863 --> 00:17:25,692
My arm's injured today,
so I won't cuff you.

410
00:17:25,693 --> 00:17:26,813
Take him back.

411
00:17:27,053 --> 00:17:27,972
Don't be rash.

412
00:17:27,973 --> 00:17:28,212
Wait.

413
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:29,732
Dazhuang, go back and inform them.

414
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:30,252
Hurry!

415
00:17:30,253 --> 00:17:30,983
Wait.

416
00:17:31,103 --> 00:17:32,732
- There goes that temper again.
- You brat!

417
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:35,012
I swear I'm going to use torture on you.

418
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:36,293
I swear I will.

419
00:17:36,693 --> 00:17:37,732
Confess!

420
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,692
Fine. I will.

421
00:17:38,693 --> 00:17:39,772
I'll confess.

422
00:17:39,773 --> 00:17:40,772
I'm an honest man.

423
00:17:40,773 --> 00:17:42,463
You know I am honest.

424
00:17:42,943 --> 00:17:43,342
But

425
00:17:43,343 --> 00:17:45,053
what exactly do you want me to confess?

426
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:46,743
Tell me.

427
00:17:47,253 --> 00:17:48,533
What did you say about me?

428
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,342
- Bring out the torture.
- No!

429
00:17:54,343 --> 00:17:54,942
Talk or not?

430
00:17:54,943 --> 00:17:56,182
Wait.

431
00:17:56,183 --> 00:17:57,452
Officer!

432
00:17:57,453 --> 00:17:58,492
Young Master.

433
00:17:58,493 --> 00:18:00,342
I honestly didn't say
anything bad about you.

434
00:18:00,343 --> 00:18:02,212
I just said your family's wealthy,

435
00:18:02,213 --> 00:18:03,492
you're generous,

436
00:18:03,493 --> 00:18:05,052
and you spend money like it's nothing.

437
00:18:05,053 --> 00:18:06,093
I...

438
00:18:06,663 --> 00:18:08,183
You think I'm an idiot?

439
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:10,052
What's that supposed to mean?
What do you mean?

440
00:18:10,053 --> 00:18:11,142
An idiot?

441
00:18:11,143 --> 00:18:12,293
You're just...

442
00:18:13,013 --> 00:18:13,492
No.

443
00:18:13,493 --> 00:18:15,052
I mean

444
00:18:15,053 --> 00:18:17,142
your taste for antiques

445
00:18:17,143 --> 00:18:17,972
is second to none.

446
00:18:17,973 --> 00:18:20,212
No one's got a better eye than you.
I'm giving you credit.

447
00:18:20,213 --> 00:18:23,093
You're the expert.

448
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:24,943
That's it?

449
00:18:25,493 --> 00:18:26,373
Uh.

450
00:18:26,453 --> 00:18:27,102
That's it?

451
00:18:27,103 --> 00:18:28,263
That's all.

452
00:18:28,453 --> 00:18:29,252
Torture him!

453
00:18:29,253 --> 00:18:29,532
Uh!

454
00:18:29,533 --> 00:18:31,122
Alright, I'll talk!

455
00:18:31,123 --> 00:18:34,043
(End of Episode 28)

456
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,040
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

457
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,580
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

458
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:38,830
♪However, the world changes♪

459
00:18:38,830 --> 00:18:40,750
♪You'll still be by my side♪

460
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:42,440
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

461
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,010
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

462
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:45,580
♪If this is my final chapter♪

463
00:18:45,580 --> 00:18:48,080
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
